 pangaea he proposed that all the land masses on earth were once united in a giant supercontinent during the paleozoic in the mesozoic eras now what exactly is pangea hopefully this animation will start to work but pangaea means all earth or all land wagner believed that pangaea broke part forming the continents in the oceans as we know them today he theorized that pangaea consisted of two major parts larasia in the north and gondwana in the south today eurasia and north america are the remnants of eurasia and south america africa india and australia and antarctica form the principal fragments of gondwana so wegner's notion of continental drift was the fragmentation of pangaea and the slow movement of continents away from the supercontinent this hypothesis was based on much more than just the match between continental outlines noticed by many others such as the most famously sir francis bacon all the way in the 1600s even you as children probably looked at a map of the world and thought gee these continents look like puzzle pieces they must have gone together but that wasn't the only evidence wegner had fenger gathered a lot of circumstantial evidence as well closely related fossil plants and animals that seem likely to evolve in the same geographic region were now scattered across south africa south america india australia and even antarctica paleozoic and mesozoic rock formations also seemed closely related though they are now separated by the atlantic and indian oceans so again we have lots of evidence supporting continental drift that the continental jigsaw puzzle and that identical fossil organisms were found on multiple continents again africa south america india antarctica and australia which are now separated by massive oceans so how did the animals cross the vast oceans well a lot of people had theories about this they thought maybe they rafted across the oceans but probably the most likely reason is that the continents had to have moved themselves not only